{
  "texts": [
    "The non-trivial OPE is [αK, S] = 2α z=0 dz w=z dw ∂Φ(w)e -2Φ β(z) = -2αS.",
    "form G + 0 G+ 0 ΛF00vanish inside the correlation function.",
    "Overall, the general form for the n-point correlation function of the hybrid formalism for genus g ≥ 1 is[7,23] (g - 11-ℓ)(-iσ) + (n + 2g -2 + ℓ)(-2ρ -iσ -iH) + (g -1)(ρ + iH) + n(2ρ + iσ + iH) + ℓ(ρ + iH 1) + ℓ(ρ + iH 2) = -(g -1)(3ρ + 3iσ + iH), Alinear dilaton can be described by the action S = -ϵ 2π d 2 z ∂ϕ ∂ϕ, for ϵ = ±1, which implies the OPE ϕ(z)ϕ(w) ∼ ϵ log(z -w).",
    "See also[17].",
    "We will use the term \"minimal tension\", rather than \"tensionless\" to describe this string theory."
  ]
}